    mdxType: "MDXLayout"
  }), mdx("p", null, "The craftsperson and the pragmatist, in the context of this article, are two absolutist caricatures of a software developer with respect to how they approach and solve problems. They exist on opposite ends of a spectrum while real people facing real problems will fall somewhere in the middle. Our position on the spectrum between pragmatist and craftsperson is not static but rather constantly changing based on our own experiences and the demands of the company or project we work on."), mdx("p", null, "This article is not meant to be prescriptive or carry any intention on how you should do your work. The intention is to draw attention towards these different styles of work so that we may reflect on which combination is best suited to the work that we face."), mdx("h2", {
